Is your exhaust stinky, like its running rich?  You really have fuel 
spraying out of the breather cap?!

> One more question, water coming from the exhaust?  I know lots of cars 
> do
> this but now that it9s getting cold, mine does it and never used to.

Water is a by-product of combustion.  Once your engine gets up to 
operating temperature, it will burn it off better.  When it's colder 
outside, the water vapor is more likely to condense at the tailpipe.

